OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1773745531
OL,3,C'Thought I was going to die':
OL,4,CInvestigation reveals reality of
OL,5,Ccorridor care
OL,7,FThe longest individual corridor stay
OL,8,Fhowever was recorded at Ysbyty Gwynedd
OL,9,Fin 2024, with one patient spending
OL,10,Fmore than five days on a corridor.
OL,12,FOne nurse at Ysbyty Gwynedd, who spoke
OL,13,Fanonymously, said treating patients in
OL,14,Fcorridors has become "normal" and
OL,15,Fdescribed corridor care as a "crisis".
OL,17,F"It's every day. It's daily now. You
OL,18,Fgo to work expecting it," they said.
OL,26,@vD@VOUvD@]O]wD@^OUwD@eO]yD@AOUzD@YO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/21
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1773745531
OL,3,C'Thought I was going to die':
OL,4,CInvestigation reveals reality of
OL,5,Ccorridor care
OL,7,F"It feels like a crisis at the moment
OL,8,Fand the last two months have really
OL,9,Ffelt like a crisis."
OL,11,FThe nurse said it was impossible to
OL,12,Fdeliver the standard of care that
OL,13,Fstaff aim for when patients are
OL,14,Ftreated in corridors.
OL,16,F"I'm sure things are being missed
OL,17,Fbecause there's no way you can get the
OL,18,Fbest care when you're a patient on a
OL,19,Fcorridor," they said.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@TO]xD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/21
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1773745531
OL,3,C'Thought I was going to die':
OL,4,CInvestigation reveals reality of
OL,5,Ccorridor care
OL,7,F"You do the best you can but it's not
OL,8,Fto standard.
OL,10,F"As an experienced nurse, you
OL,11,Fsometimes feel guilty that you have to
OL,12,Fignore someone because it's so busy on
OL,13,Fthe corridor.
OL,15,F"All I can say is the staff are
OL,16,Fgenuinely doing their best, they
OL,17,Freally are trying but it's not good
OL,18,Fenough just to rely on that. Something
OL,19,Fneeds to change."
OL,21,F'Unacceptable'
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@AOUwD@AOU{D@QO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/21
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1773745531
OL,3,C'Thought I was going to die':
OL,4,CInvestigation reveals reality of
OL,5,Ccorridor care
OL,7,FDr Phil White, Deputy Chair of the
OL,8,FWelsh Council of the British Medical
OL,9,FAssociation, said the situation was
OL,10,Funacceptable.
OL,12,F"We've been saying for some time as a
OL,13,Fmedical association that this is
OL,14,Funacceptable, it's dangerous for
OL,15,Fpatients," he said.
OL,17,F"There simply aren't enough staff to
OL,18,Fcope with the workload."
OL,20,FHe also raised concerns about patient
OL,21,Fdignity and monitoring.
OL,26,@tD@AOUwD@JO]yD@AOUzD@XO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/21
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1773745531
OL,3,C'Thought I was going to die':
OL,4,CInvestigation reveals reality of
OL,5,Ccorridor care
OL,7,FHe continued: "First of all, there's
OL,8,Fno privacy when you're receiving
OL,9,Ftreatment like this. You would at
OL,10,Fleast want to be behind curtains but
OL,11,Fthese patients are just on display
OL,12,Falong the corridor.
OL,14,F"It's not fair. There's no dignity
OL,15,Fthere at all.
OL,17,F"Some of these patients are on drips,
OL,18,Fmaybe antibiotics, and people in those
OL,19,Fcircumstances need to be monitored -
OL,20,Fwhich is very difficult for staff."
OL,26,@oD@OOUvD@AOUyD@AOU|D@cO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/21
